==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eyeful
<hw>Eye"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Filling or satisfying
the eye; visible; remarkable.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Eyeful</xex> trophies.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>eyeful</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: eyeful
<hw>eye"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a view of
something remarkable; a completely satisfying view; as much as, or more
than, one would want to see; <as>as, he got an <ex>eyeful</ex> of
burnt-out buildings on his tour of the south Bronx</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an unusually attractive person, especially a
beautiful woman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eyeglance</ent>⟦br⟧
